# Memory directory .gitignore — safety net for Claude per-project memory
#
# Memory lives in git (symlinked from ~/.claude/projects/<enc>/memory/ per
# .claude/signoff-protocol.md Step 2), which means it gets pushed to GitHub.
# This file is the first line of defense against accidentally committing
# secrets or local-only convenience files.
#
# Adding more patterns as the project evolves is encouraged.
# REMOVING patterns requires a real reason — get Jim's sign-off.

# Env files (any variant)
*.env
*.env.*
.env*

# Secret-shaped names (lowercase + common capitalizations)
*secret*
*Secret*
*SECRET*
*token*
*Token*
*TOKEN*
*credential*
*Credential*
*CREDENTIAL*
*password*
*Password*
*PASSWORD*
*api-key*
*api_key*
*apikey*

# Keys & certs
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.cer
*.crt
*-private.json
*-credentials.json
*service-account*.json

# Local-only convenience
*.local
*.private
*.tmp
*.temp
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Anything explicitly marked as do-not-commit
DO-NOT-COMMIT*
do-not-commit*
NO-COMMIT*
no-commit*
